    "By partially substituting the chalcogen anion S with oxygen elements O, resulting in a general formula of Ca 6 Sn 4 S 14-x O x (CSSO x, x from 1 to 5), the synthesized materials exhibit enhanced performance 47.",
    "Through theoretical analysis, we designate CSSO 4 -0980 as the target structure for its optimal performance, while the notably inefficient derivative structure CSSO 3 -072 is selected as the starting structure for this RL task (Supplementary Section 5).",
    "Analogous to the high-dimensional space cliff walking task, the objective of this task is to identify the optimal synthesis route from the starting structure to the target structure, within the state space composed of all 3472 CSSO x derivative structures.",
